---
title: Aspect Ratio Box
description: Maintain a fixed aspect ratio on any element using the `aspect-ratio` property.
slug: aspect-ratio-box
cssFile: aspect-ratio-box.css
explanation: The <code>aspect-ratio</code> property makes an element maintain a width-to-height ratio automatically. Set a width (fixed, percentage, or auto) and the height adjusts to match the ratio. This replaces the old padding-top hack (<code>padding-top:56.25%</code> for 16:9) with a clean, readable one-liner.
---
{% extends "example.njk" %}
{% block demo %}
<div class="ratio-grid">
	<div class="ratio-box ratio-16-9">16 / 9</div>
	<div class="ratio-box ratio-1-1">1 / 1</div>
	<div class="ratio-box ratio-4-3">4 / 3</div>
</div>
{% endblock %}

{% block html_code %}
{%- highlight "html" %}
<div class="box-16-9">16:9 video</div>
<div class="box-square">Square</div>
<div class="box-4-3">4:3 image</div>
{%- endhighlight %}
{% endblock %}

{% block css_code %}
{%- highlight "css" %}
/* Set width, height is auto-calculated */
.box-16-9 {
  aspect-ratio: 16 / 9;
  width: 100%;
}

.box-square {
  aspect-ratio: 1 / 1;
  width: 200px;
}

.box-4-3 {
  aspect-ratio: 4 / 3;
  width: 300px;
}
{%- endhighlight %}
{% endblock %}
